               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182107180056"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t18210718-137-person1203">
                  FRANCIS 
                  BARRS
               <interp inst="t18210718-137-person1203" type="surname" value="BARRS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210718-137-person1203" type="given" value="FRANCIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210718-137-person1203" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On Sunday, the 8th of July, I heard a noise in my house, and lost this sheet. A few days after the prisoner passed my house. M'Donald pointed the prisoner out.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210718-137-person1204">
                  MARGARET 
                  M'DONALD
               <interp inst="t18210718-137-person1204" type="surname" value="M'DONALD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210718-137-person1204" type="given" value="MARGARET"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210718-137-person1204" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was going on an errand, and saw the prisoner go out of the house with a bundle. I told the prosecutrix. It was about seven o'clock in the morning. My mother missed the sheet when she went down stairs, and told Barrs.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210718-137-person1205">
                  GEORGE 
                  WILSON
               <interp inst="t18210718-137-person1205" type="surname" value="WILSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210718-137-person1205" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210718-137-person1205" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was sent for, and took her at Barrs' house; and, in going to the office, she said she took it, and cut part of it up for a pinafore for her child, and the rest for a shirt for her brother. I found one on her brother's back, made out of it.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
